    # game/areas/prologue.rpy:1311
    old "“The people here are... Disquieting.” Every few words, she taps the table with her finger. “Their traditions won’t help them negotiate with the officials. Here,” she starts to draw lines with her index finger, as if she’s pointing at an invisible map. “The peninsula is connected with roads, like a big circle. In the northwest, you’ll find a weird village at a bog. It’s not exactly pagan, I don’t think, it even has a priest who claims to be an Eremite[custom1] \n\n“They do crazy shit,” {color=#f6d6bd}her companion{/color} chips in. “They use the dead to cut down trees and dig in soil. Once I saw it, I begged to never return there.” "
