    # game/areas/prologue.rpy:1420
    old "“If anyone knows, they won’t tell us. Maybe someone is keeping him in a basement,” {color=#f6d6bd}the man{/color} carves with passion. “We haven’t seen him, or his saurian. Something ate them, I bet. The officials have hired {i}you{/i}, right? They don’t expect him to return.” \n\nRicher roadwardens often use four-legged, meat-eating saurians as their mounts. They have to be tamed and trained since their hatching, but, unlike horses, can easily defend themselves from many monsters. [custom1] "
