    old "You’re surrounded by sunlight, your back begs you to stand up. \n\nBefore you fully wake up, you smell a roast. No, burning meat. Burning, rotten meat. Disgust crawls toward your consciousness. \n\nYou stand up. Normally you would dust off your cape and blanket, but your instincts are stronger than your routine. \n\nYour horse is looking around nervously. Your bags are where you had left them. You see an open gate. "
