    # game/areas/prologue.rpy:2035
    old "You can’t enter the forest blindly. If these or other creatures were to chase after you, the thicket would be disastrous for your horse. There are reasons why travelers stay as close to the main roads as possible, and why adventurers move in groups. \n\nUsually, the safest approach would be to stay where you are and just wait for the pack to get hungry. It may, however, take up to a couple of hours. You’re thinking about your conversation with {color=#f6d6bd}Tulia{/color}. You’ve got a lot to do, and time may be of the essence. "
